  "text": "Below, we will provide sufficient conditions in terms of LMIs under which system (17), and thus the NCS model (10) (due to (19)), with a given periodic protocol satisfying (12), is EISS. To do so, let us introduce the set of matrices R given by R = {diag(r 1 I 1 , . . . , r K I K , r K+1 I 1 , . . . , r 2K I K , r 2K+1 I 1 , . . . , r 3K I K ) | r i > 0 for i ∈ {1, . . . , 3K}}, (22) in which K is related to the total number of real Jordan blocks of A p , see [CITATION_1] .",
